- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely because the paper discusses the trade-off between memory and time complexity in building a grammar that generates a given string. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility because the paper uses a learning-based approach to build the grammar, but it is less likely because the focus is on compression rather than prediction or classification. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility because the paper deals with the size of the grammar relative to the size of the input string, which is a fundamental question in information theory. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible because the paper uses a streaming model, which is relevant to the study of large-scale data processing in networked systems.
